Interface IQueue<T extends Comparable<T>>

All Known Implementing Classes:

public interface IQueue<T extends Comparable<T>>
Implementation of the Queue ADT. Uses interface to simulate basic operations of a Queue.

    • ToArray

      T[] ToArray(T[] arrayType)
      Converts the list into array.
      Parameters:
      arrayType - : Type of array to sort (must be the same type as defined). This parameter accepts an instance of previously-defined-type array.

      Example: if the list holds Integer, then Integer[] array = list.ToArray(new Integer[0])

      Returns:
      T[] : Representation of the list as array. null if the list is empty
      Throws:
      NullPointerException - If there is null node in the list.
